CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 23, 1958, page 7, reads: "Science Grant Recipient - Arthur A. Wall poses with his wife, Evelyn, and daughter, Brenda, shortly after being informed that he had received a National Science Foundation grant to study and do research in teaching of chemistry at the University of Virginia at Charlottesville, Va., beginning in September of this year. Mr. Wall is a native of Rankin, but now resides in Portsmouth, Va. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Arthur A. Wall, recipient of National Science Foundation grant, his wife Evelyn Wall, and daughter Brenda Wall, posed in domestic interior with floral sofa and curtains
